    "caption": "The world's most famous bamboo expert, eating sixteen hours a day.",
    "shortDescription": "Giant pandas are technically carnivores — classified as meat-eaters — but they eat almost nothing but bamboo, which is so low in nutrition that they have to eat enormous piles of it, all day long. They have a special wrist bone that juts out like a thumb, perfectly shaped for gripping stalks. Fun fact: A giant panda eats up to thirty-eight kilograms of bamboo in a single day — that's roughly the weight of an average seven-year-old."
